Cookie:<br><br>
You talk about the honor that comes OFF the battlefield... and you do a good job!<br><br>
But... how about the honor that was carried ONTO the battlefield.  You know what I mean.  That loose bag of stuff that was given to us by football coaches, small town cop, local preacher, Roy Rogers, Batman, school teachers, big brothers...Dads... uncles... and Grandpa... And Grandma, Mom, sunday school teachers,... and the pretty girls.<br><br>
Yep!  We carried stuff into battle, Cookie... good stuff... stuff that managed to keep some of us alive.  The tragedy is that some good Bros died with their good stuff... except for the good stuff they gave us before they checked out.<br><br>
Well, I guess we just packed it down (honor) into a heavy, barely manageable, giant brick... too big to carry sometimes... too complex to explain... too valuable to lay down... and we staggered off the battlefields of our minds with it strapped to our backs.<br><br>
You and all the others answered the call... went forward with a novice's appreciation of honor and you came home as clarion examples of honor.<br><br>
The young men and women... little children playing at our feet... who may be called to put their lives on the line for our way of life will likely have a bunch of stuff from old medics, gun bunnies, shit burners, cannon cockers, grunts... and maybe even smart assed fly boys and bird men to put in their own bags... before they step into harms way.<br><br>
Those fortunate enough to know all the guys on this site will have a lot of good stuff (honor) to select from.<br><br>
Those who know of Cook Barela will be priviledged!<br><br>
Hecito Yelo, Mita Kola... Cetan, Akicita Was'te<br><br>
P.S.  listen to your dreams....Listen to the Creator!<br>

